article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. -- — Latrell Reid's 21 points helped Saint Peter's defeat Siena 63-52 on Sunday. Reid was 9-of-21 shooting and 3 of 5 from the free-throw line for the Peacocks (11-7, 7-2 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Roy Clarke scored 10 points and added eight rebounds. Brent Bland had nine points and shot 3 for 8, including 1 for 4 from beyond the arc. Zek Tekin led the Saints (3-17, 2-7) in scoring, finishing with 22 points and two steals. Giovanni Emejuru added 11 points and eight rebounds for Siena. Sveinn Birgisson also had eight points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
